titles.title: A bill to suspend temporarily the duty on certain chemicals.

action.text: Sponsor introductory remarks on measure. (CR S10922)
Read twice and referred to the Committee on Finance.

bill.summary: 8/6/1993--Introduced. Amends the Harmonized Tariff Schedule of the United States to suspend, through December 31, 1996, the duty on: (1) (R)-a-amino-1,4-cyclohexadiene-1-acetic acid; (2) (R)-a-amino-4-hydroxybenzeneacetic acid; (3) (R)-a-amino benzene-acetic acid; (4) N,N'-bis(trimethylsilyl) urea; (5) penicillin V potassium; and (6) penicillin G potassium.
